						               													<description>THE CARD TOWER&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players: 2 or 4&amp;#10;Game time: 15 to 25 min&amp;#10;Age group: 10+&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Synopsis&amp;#10;The Card Tower is a Dice/Card game where 2 to 4 construction companies are competing against each other to win a lucrative contract to build the next luxury tower in downtown Manhattan.  During each turn the companies are trying to build each of the four construction zones of the building floor plan faster than their opponent.  During the construction phase each company has a saboteur who is trying to stop the other companies from completing their job.  As the tower rises, by placing a new tower card on top of the previous card with dice, it&amp;rsquo;s up to you to decide what&amp;rsquo;s more important; building a zone of the floor plan or sabotaging your opponent.  If you build the most high quality sections of the tower, you will win the contact and the honor of putting your name of the tower.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As you play you are actually building a tower of cards with dice becoming the supporting structure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Components&amp;#10;18 &amp;ndash; Tower cards&amp;#10;18 &amp;ndash; Sabotage cards&amp;#10;36 &amp;ndash; d6 dice &amp;ldquo;9 dice each of four colors&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
